title: The satsu
author: seppuku2020
pages:
#- The satsuma rebellion

§0in early 2020 yamato was becoming a popular place to set up shop by international tradesmen. One by one ugly shops spawned in honshu, selling various tools at extortionate prices§r
#- tools that yamato could already produce by themselves. kamikaze_san, an admiral in the yamato imperial navy, became very triggered as he felt the simple way of the samurai was being desecrated. "yamato was better when it was just me and james" he thought.
#- admiral kamikaze decided to form his own shogunate where the way of the samurai would be upheld, far away from the globalised trade hub that honshu was becoming. Emporer james agreed to the split and offered kamikaze his own piece of land to the west
#- Kamikaze made his way to the island on an overcast and rainy day at night. and contemplated what it would become. he had hoped that by forming the new shogunate emporer james would repent of his trade policy, and he continued to bitch about the situation 
#- on discord until one fateful day when even james realised that the way of the samurai was starting to be lost and after a heart to heart kamikaze decided to return safe in the knowledge that the samurai spirit remained in honshu
#- 